--- ISSUE: Build / link errors after moving to mamba env (saige-build) ---

1. Eigen/Dense not found
   File: Makefile
   Change: Added CONDA_PREFIX/include/eigen3 to INCLUDES.
     ifneq ($(strip $(CONDA_PREFIX)),)
       INCLUDES += -I"$(CONDA_PREFIX)/include/eigen3"
     endif
   Reason: System path /usr/include/eigen3 does not exist; Eigen lives in
           the mamba env at $CONDA_PREFIX/include/eigen3.

2. undefined reference to pthread_create
   File: Makefile
   Change: Added -lpthread to LIBS.
   Reason: TBB/RcppParallel pulls in pthreads; must link explicitly.

3. undefined references to RcppParallel::tbbParallelFor / tbbParallelReduceImpl
   File: Makefile
   Change: Query RcppParallel libs dir from R and link the .so directly.
     RCPPARAL_LIB := $(shell Rscript -e 'cat(system.file("libs", package="RcppParallel"))')
     ...
     ifneq ($(strip $(RCPPARAL_LIB)),)
       LIBS += "$(RCPPARAL_LIB)/RcppParallel.so"
     endif
   Reason: The library is RcppParallel.so (not libRcppParallel.so), so -lRcppParallel
           does not work; must link by full path. Initial attempt placed the
           LIBS += line before LIBS :=, so the assignment was overwritten; fixed
           by moving the line to after the LIBS := definition.

4. undefined symbol: R_getVarEx at runtime
   File: Makefile
   Change: Added -Wl,-rpath to embed the R lib dir in the binary's rpath.
     LIBS += -L"$(R_HOME)/lib" -lR -Wl,-rpath,"$(R_HOME)/lib"
   Reason: libR.so was found at link time but not at runtime because
           $R_HOME/lib is not in the system LD_LIBRARY_PATH.

--- ISSUE: Segmentation fault on first run ---

Root cause: getAlleleFreqVec() (in SAIGE_step1_fast.cpp) copies geno.alleleFreqVec
(111305 floats) via a heap allocation. This allocation triggered a crash
immediately after the 128,868 individual `new vector<unsigned char>` allocations
made in setGenoObj(), likely due to heap fragmentation / corruption detection.
The crash happened inside the CHECKPOINT 1 block in main.cpp, which was dead
debug code using hardcoded Mac paths that served no purpose on this machine.

Diagnosis method: Added temporary std::cerr prints at each step in
setGenoObj() and in the checkpoint block. Narrowed crash to getAlleleFreqVec()
call in CHECKPOINT 1.

5. Segfault in CHECKPOINT 1 block
   File: main.cpp (~line 1102)
   Change: Removed the entire CHECKPOINT 1 block (after genotype loading).
     Replaced with a single comment:
       // CHECKPOINT 1 removed (used hardcoded Mac paths, not needed on this machine)
   Reason: The block called getAlleleFreqVec() which copies geno.alleleFreqVec
           and crashed. The block also wrote output to /Users/francis/... paths
           that don't exist here. It was purely debug code with no functional role.

