--- ISSUE: Segfault in quantitative GLMM solver (getPCG1ofSigmaAndVector) ---
Date: 2026-03-10

Root cause: Armadillo ABI mismatch between translation units on Linux/conda.
The original code was written on macOS where Homebrew's system armadillo and
RcppArmadillo's bundled armadillo happen to be the same file (same include path).
On Linux/conda, the system armadillo (/envs/saige-build/include/armadillo) and
RcppArmadillo's bundled armadillo (.../RcppArmadillo/include/current/armadillo)
are different files with different include guards. Headers using <armadillo> got
the system version; files using <RcppArmadillo.h> got the bundled version.
Although both are v15.2.3 with identical struct layouts, the two template
instantiations have different ARMA_EXTRA_MAT_PROTO / ARMA_DONT_USE_WRAPPER
defines, causing undefined behavior when arma::fvec objects cross the TU
boundary through the shim. Observed: [SHIM] w.n=1 tau.n=1 v.n=1 instead of
correct sizes, leading to segfault inside gen_spsolve_v4 / arma::spsolve.

Also found separately: -O3 optimization causes a SuperLU crash (arma::spsolve
via dgssv). ASAN build at -O1 completed successfully, confirming optimizer bug.

7. Segfault: Armadillo ABI mismatch (Linux/conda platform fix)
   Files: saige_ai.hpp, saige_shims.hpp, score.hpp,
          glmm.cpp, null_model_engine.cpp, main.cpp
   Change: Replaced all `#include <armadillo>` with `#include <RcppArmadillo.h>`
     so every TU uses the same RcppArmadillo-bundled armadillo headers.
   Reason: On macOS (original platform), <armadillo> and <RcppArmadillo.h>
     resolve to the same armadillo. On Linux/conda they are different files,
     causing ABI-incompatible arma::fvec objects across TU boundaries.

8. Segfault: -O3 optimization crashes SuperLU inside arma::spsolve
   File: Makefile
   Change: CXXFLAGS -O3 -> -O2
     CXXFLAGS ?= -std=c++17 -O2 -DARMA_64BIT_WORD=1 ...
   Reason: At -O3 the SuperLU dgssv call inside arma::spsolve crashes.
     Confirmed by ASAN build at -O1 completing without error. -O2 is stable.

